flowRoot.flowPara: Aim of the game:
Each player should seek to include card like their objective card within the IN set, and ensure cards that differ are excluded in the OUT set. The cards on top are scored at the end of the game.
Set up:

Deal each player a single card. This is placed face up in front of them. This is their objective card. Deal five more cards for each player, face down. This is their hand. The remaining cards form the deck.
Order of play:

The player to the left of the dealer starts. Play proceeds clockwise. On their turn, each player lays a card from their hand on the IN or the OUT pile, and picks another card up from the deck. The game ends when all players have empty hands.
Aim of the game:
Each player should seek to include card like their objective card within the IN set, and ensure cards that differ are excluded in the OUT set. The cards on top are scored at the end of the game.
Set up:

Deal each player a single card. This is placed face up in front of them. This is their objective card. Deal five more cards for each player, face down. This is their hand. The remaining cards form the deck.
Order of play:

The player to the left of the dealer starts. Play proceeds clockwise. On their turn, each player lays a card from their hand on the IN or the OUT pile, and picks another card up from the deck. The game ends when all players have empty hands.
At end of play, the top IN cards give you points according to their resemblance to your objective:
+ 1 for each card of the same suit
+ 3 for each card of the same rank
- 1 for each card of the same suit
- 3 for each card of the same rank

Jack or Queen:
Choose another player to pick up two cards from the opposite set to which this is played.
King:
Force any player to discard their hand into either the IN or OUT set, according to your wish.
Ace:
Force any player to discard their objective card into the IN or OUT deck and pick a new one from the main deck.
Joker:
An entirely free move. You can do whatever you want, ignoring all other rules of the game.
